<font face="verdana"> 
<div> 

 
 The West Farms Workforce1 Career Center has partnered with various retail stores to recruit qualified individuals for their stores in New York City. They are seeking outgoing and dynamic individuals with exceptional customer service skills.
 <br> <br>

<b>Shift Leaders :</b> 
<ul><li>Must be able to develop and lead team members for a specific area of the store with a strong influence throughout the store and deliver great customer service. 
<li>Provide general responsibility for the store in the absence of the assistant manager. This includes, but is not limited to store financial performance, cash control, inventory, safety, customer service and management of entire staff. 
<li>Support assistant managers in the execution of all company initiatives.
 </ul>

<b>Store Associates :</b> 
<ul><li> Provide exceptional service to customers which includes greeting customers, assisting them with selection of merchandise, completing transactions, and answering questions regarding the store and merchandise. 
 </ul>

<b>Requirements :</b>
<li>Ability to follow directives and interpret retail operational documents as assigned. </li>
<li> Prefer experience working in retail, or drug store environments.</li>
<li> Ability to regularly lift up to 40 lbs. (and occasionally, up to 55 lbs.) from floor level to above shoulder height; must be able to meet demands of frequent walking, standing, stooping, kneeling, climbing, pushing, pulling, and repetitive lifting, with or without reasonable accommodation.</li>
<li> Ability to work flexible, full-time schedule to include days, evenings, weekends and holidays.
<li><b> OPEN AVAILABILITY A MUST<b>
<p>
<b>In order to apply and be considered for these positions, interested candidates must attend a screening interview conducted by West Farms Workforce1 Career Center at a recruitment event below.</b><br><br>
<b>Days:<b> Monday 03/13/2017<br><br>
<b>Check in:</b> 10:00 AM - 10:15 AM (No admittance after 10:15 AM)<br><br>
 
<b>OR<p>
<b>Days:</b> Wednesday 03/15/2017 - Thursday 03/16/2017 <br><br>
<b>Check in:</b> 1:00 PM - 1:15 PM ( No admittance after 10:15 AM)<br><br>
<b>Location:</b> 901 East Tremont Ave Bronx, NY 10460<br><br>
<b>Directions:</b> The entrance is on East Tremont Ave  and we are located on the 2nd floor. The closest trains are the 2/5 to WestFarms Square and closest buses are the Bx9, Bx40, Bx42, Bx36, and Bx19 
Please come with a valid photo ID, 2 copies of your resume and a pen. Professional attire is required.</p>

<hr>
<img src="http://www.nyc.gov/html/sbs/wf1/images/branding/wf1_logo_web.jpg" height="45">
<p><b><a href="http://www.nyc.gov/workforce1" rel="nofollow">Workforce1</a></b> is a service that attracts, prepares, and connects qualified candidates to job opportunities in New York City. We use a combination of recruitment expertise, industry knowledge, and services that strengthen candidates' employment prospects to make strong matches for job candidates and businesses alike.
<br><br>To learn more, visit <a href="http://www.nyc.gov/wf1recruitment" rel="nofollow">nyc.gov/wf1recruitment</a>. Don't forget to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/nycworkforce1" rel="nofollow">like us on Facebook</a>, follow <a href="http://twitter.com/nycworkforce1" rel="nofollow">@NYCWorkforce1</a>, and visit our <a href="http://nycworkforce1.org" rel="nofollow">Career Blog</a>.
<br><br> Equal opportunity employer/program. Auxiliary aids and services are available upon request to individuals with disabilities.
</p>
</b></p></b></b></b></b></li></li></li></li></li></li></div></font>    </section>

